The Cereal Growers Association has warned of food shortage if the government fails to find an urgent solution to armyworm invasion. The association said farmers have lost millions of shillings in trying to control the pest that has invaded their farms. Chairman Farnie Kruger told Agriculture CS Willy Bett that armyworm invasion led to a deficit of eight million bags this season. “The government is aware of the threat posed by the wormand we are working with state and private researchers to find a lasting solution,” Bett said. They spoke at the end of a three-day workshop in Naivasha on Sunday.  They agreed that the destruction caused by armyworm is monumental.